# 020 — TypeScript

- `strict: true` in every `tsconfig.json`. No exceptions.
- Prefer `unknown` over `any`. If `any` is unavoidable, justify with a comment.
- No `// @ts-ignore` or `// @ts-nocheck`.
- Use discriminated unions for result types: `{ success: true; data: T } | { success: false; error: AppError }`.
- All runtime validation via Zod schemas. No manual `typeof` guards for external data.
- Errors must be typed — never `throw new Error("string")` alone; wrap in typed error classes.
- Every package exposes its public API exclusively from `src/index.ts`.
- No deep internal imports across packages: `import { x } from '@adriane/graph-core'`, not `import { x } from '@adriane/graph-core/src/internal/something'`.
- Avoid `namespace`. Prefer plain module exports.
- Enums only if the values need to be iterable at runtime; prefer `const` objects + `as const` otherwise.